{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.21",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 21 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:1",
      "text": "The king’s heart is in the hand of the Lord, as the rivers of water: he turneth it whithersoever he will.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:2",
      "text": "Every way of a man is right in his own eyes: but the Lord pondereth the hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:3",
      "text": "To do justice and judgment is more acceptable to the Lord than sacrifice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:4",
      "text": "An high look, and a proud heart, and the plowing of the wicked, is sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:5",
      "text": "The thoughts of the diligent tend only to plenteousness; but of every one that is hasty only to want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:6",
      "text": "The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:7",
      "text": "The robbery of the wicked shall destroy them; because they refuse to do judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:8",
      "text": "The way of man is froward and strange: but as for the pure, his work is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:9",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in a corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman in a wide house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:10",
      "text": "The soul of the wicked desireth evil: his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:11",
      "text": "When the scorner is punished, the simple is made wise: and when the wise is instructed, he receiveth knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:12",
      "text": "The righteous man wisely considereth the house of the wicked: but God overthroweth the wicked for their wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:13",
      "text": "Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor, he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:14",
      "text": "A gift in secret pacifieth anger: and a reward in the bosom strong wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:15",
      "text": "It is joy to the just to do judgment: but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:16",
      "text": "The man that wandereth out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:17",
      "text": "He that loveth pleasure shall be a poor man: he that loveth wine and oil shall not be rich.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:18",
      "text": "The wicked shall be a ransom for the righteous, and the transgressor for the upright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:19",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and an angry woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:20",
      "text": "There is treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise; but a foolish man spendeth it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:21",
      "text": "He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:22",
      "text": "A wise man scaleth the city of the mighty, and casteth down the strength of the confidence thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:23",
      "text": "Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:24",
      "text": "Proud and haughty scorner is his name, who dealeth in proud wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:25",
      "text": "The desire of the slothful killeth him; for his hands refuse to labour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:26",
      "text": "He coveteth greedily all the day long: but the righteous giveth and spareth not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:27",
      "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is abomination: how much more, when he bringeth it with a wicked mind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:28",
      "text": "A false witness shall perish: but the man that heareth speaketh constantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:29",
      "text": "A wicked man hardeneth his face: but as for the upright, he directeth his way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:30",
      "text": "There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.21.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:31",
      "text": "The horse is prepared against the day of battle: but safety is of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
